Driver for R_Car Gen3 and Gen4 SPI Slave

Syntax:
	spi-slave-rcar [-u channel] [[-c]]

options:
	-u : select SPI channel (from 0 to 5)
	-c : set device configuration
		cpol : clock polarity (default CPOL = 0)
		cpha : clock phase    (default CPHA = 0)
		bitlen : length of 1 data element (default bitlen = 8)

Example:
	spi-slave-rcar -u2
	Above command start SPI Slave with default information: channel 2, CPOL = 0, CPHA = 0, bitlen = 8

	spi-slave-rcar -u2 -c cpol=0,cpha=1,bitlen=16
	Above command start SPI Slave channel 2 with CPOL = 0, CPHA = 1, 16 bit data
